Vladimir Putin and the risk of a third world war.
San Francisco—February 24, Vladimir Putin's invasion of Ukraine marked the beginning of a possible third world war that could destroy our civilization.
Before the invasion, Russian President Vladimir Putin and Chinese President Xi Jinping had held a long meeting on February 4, which coincided with the beginning of China's Lunar New Year celebrations and the opening of the Beijing Winter Olympics.
After the meeting, they issued a carefully drafted 5,000-word document declaring the establishment of a close partnership between the two countries.
This document is far more powerful than any treaty, and definitely requires careful negotiation beforehand.
I am shocked that Xi seems to have given Putin a free hand to invade and wage war on Ukraine.
He thinks that the confirmation of his status as China's lifetime ruler this year is merely a formality, and he is undoubtedly confident about it.
